#* {{quote-book|en|year=2002|author={{w|Colin Jones (historian)|Colin Jones}}|title=The Great Nation|publisher=Penguin|year_published=2003|page=30|passage=He never, it should be noted, totally renounced his inheritance: a critic of the court round, he benefited to the tune of a cool two million '''livres''' a year from royal largesse {{...}}.}}
