==English==
[[File:Runic letter ansuz.png|thumb|100px|Runic letter {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr||ᚫ|tr=a|ansuz}}, source for Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letters replaced by ''A'']]

===Etymology 1===
From {{der-lite|en|enm|-}} and {{der-lite|en|ang|-}} upper case letter {{m-lite|enm|A}} and split of {{der-lite|en|enm|-}} and {{der-lite|en|ang|-}} upper case letter {{m-lite|enm|Æ}}.
* The {{der-lite|en|ang|-}} letters {{m-lite|ang|sc=Latinx|A}} and {{m-lite|ang|sc=Latinx|Æ}} replaced the Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letters {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr|ᚪ||tr=a|āc}} and {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr|ᚫ||tr=æ|æsc}}, derived from the Runic letter {{m-lite|mul|sc=Runr|ᚫ||tr=a|Ansuz}}, in the 7th century.

====Alternative forms====
* {{qualifier|Gregg shorthand versions [[w:Gregg Shorthand#Centennial Gregg Shorthand|Centennial]], [[w:Gregg Shorthand#Series 90 Gregg Shorthand|Series 90]], [[w:Gregg Shorthand#Diamond Jubilee Gregg Shorthand|DJS]], [[w:Gregg Shorthand#Simplified Gregg Shorthand|Simplified]], [[w:Gregg Shorthand#Anniversary Gregg Shorthand|Anniversary]], and [[w:Gregg Shorthand#Pre-Anniversary Gregg Shorthand|Pre-Anniversary]]}} {{l-lite|mul|·||dot}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{qualifier|letter name}}
** {{a|RP|GenAm}} {{IPA-lite|en|/eɪ̯/}}
** {{audio|en|en-us-a.ogg|Audio (US)}}
** {{a|AusE}} {{IPA-lite|en|/æɪ/}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪ|s=1}}
*: The current pronunciation is a comparatively modern sound, and has taken the place of what, till about the early part of the 15th century, was similar to that in other languages.

